Acoustic Connect for Cordova

New Features

- Unified `AcousticConnect` JavaScript API (Promise-based), available both as a
  CommonJS/ES module export and as a global `window.AcousticConnect`
- `AcousticConnect.enable(appKey, postURL, pushMode?, options?)` — initializes the
  native iOS and Android Connect SDKs
- `AcousticConnect.logIdentity(...)` — logs identity signals (e.g. login,
  registration) to Connect
- `AcousticConnect.push` namespace — permission requests (`requestPermission`,
  `getPermissionState`) and manual-mode forwarders (`didReceiveNotification`,
  `didReceiveResponse`) for apps that own their own native push delegate
- `AcousticConnect.setLogLevel(...)` and `AcousticConnect.disable()`
- Automatic and manual push modes, selectable via `enable()`
- `ConnectConfig.json`-driven configuration, including a `useRelease` flag that
  switches between debug/release native SDK variants with no build-time flag
- TypeScript type definitions shipped with the package
- Sample Cordova app (`applications/Demo`) demonstrating setup end-to-end


Known Issues

- Rich push cannot be end-to-end tested on the iOS Simulator — simulators don't display large icon.

Our environment for this release:

- Xcode 26.2
- MacOS 26.0.1
- iOS 15.1 to 26.x
- Android minSdk 26, SDK 36
